                                                            <comment id="89204" author="712020:c31907b0-e8a3-4790-8686-3585fdb11873" created="Tue, 23 Jun 2026 12:47:00 -0700"  >&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;QAVerificationSteps%28TaskT4%E2%80%94envlevel%2Cblackbox%29&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;QA Verification Steps (Task T4 &#8212; env-level, black-box)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The unit tests in PR #283 prove the logic with the SFTP boundary stubbed. This T4 pass proves it end-to-end against a real deployed Treasury service. The failure is config-inducible &#8212; no test harness needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Environment:&lt;/em&gt; Dev or SBOX (NOT prod). Treasury API deployed + reachable, App Insights accessible, and &lt;tt&gt;notifications:settlement:recipients&lt;/tt&gt; pointed at a team-reachable inbox.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Preconditions:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;FundingBatches&lt;/tt&gt; rows staged with &lt;tt&gt;BatchFileName IS NOT NULL&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;RequestSentTimeStamp IS NULL&lt;/tt&gt; &#8212; stage &lt;em&gt;&#8805;3 rows&lt;/em&gt; to exercise the multi-batch &quot;stop and enumerate&quot; case.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a &lt;em&gt;banking day&lt;/em&gt; (otherwise &lt;tt&gt;IsBankingDay()&lt;/tt&gt; skips the loop).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Trigger the failure (pick one):&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Natural%3ADev%2FSBOXcurrentlyreproducethe%7B%7BSocketException%7D%7DviatheWorldpaysourceIPallowlistgap%E2%80%94justcall%7B%7BPOSTsendfundingbatch%7D%7Dasis.&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Natural: Dev/SBOX currently reproduce the &lt;tt&gt;SocketException&lt;/tt&gt; via the Worldpay source-IP allowlist gap &#8212; just call &lt;tt&gt;POST send-funding-batch&lt;/tt&gt; as-is.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Deterministic%28SocketException%29%3Apoint%7B%7Bprocessor%3Avantiv%3Abatch%3Asftpurl%7D%7Datanonroutablehost%E2%86%92connecttimeout.&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Deterministic (SocketException): point &lt;tt&gt;processor:vantiv:batch:sftpurl&lt;/tt&gt; at a non-routable host &#8594; connect timeout.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Deterministic%28LitleOnlineException%29%3Asetawrong%7B%7BsftpPassword%7D%7D%E2%86%92SDKwrapstheautherror.&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Deterministic (LitleOnlineException): set a wrong &lt;tt&gt;sftpPassword&lt;/tt&gt; &#8594; SDK wraps the auth error.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Which exception type was caught is not externally distinguishable by design &#8212; covered by unit tests. Use whichever trigger is convenient.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Procedure:&lt;/em&gt; stage rows &#8594; apply trigger &#8594; &lt;tt&gt;POST send-funding-batch&lt;/tt&gt; &#8594; observe &#8594; restore config and re-trigger to confirm recovery.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Pass/fail assertions:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;%28AC1%2CAC2%29ExactlyONEalertemail%3Athefailedbatchisnamed%2CALLunsentbatchesareenumerated%28Idfilename%29%2Candbatchessentbeforethefailureareabsent.&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;(AC-1, AC-2)&lt;/em&gt; Exactly ONE alert email: the failed batch is named, ALL unsent batches are enumerated (Id + filename), and batches sent before the failure are absent.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;%28AC1%29AppInsightserrorlog%28roleWellfitTreasuryAPI%29carries%7B%7BBatchId%7D%7D%2C%7B%7BBatchFileName%7D%7D%2CSFTPhost%2Candtheunsentbatchlist.&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;(AC-1)&lt;/em&gt; App Insights &lt;em&gt;error&lt;/em&gt; log (role &lt;em&gt;Wellfit Treasury API&lt;/em&gt;) carries &lt;tt&gt;BatchId&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;BatchFileName&lt;/tt&gt;, SFTP host, and the unsent-batch list.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;%28AC3%29%7B%7BRequestSentTimeStamp%7D%7DstaysNULLforthefailedstrandedrows%3Bsetforanybatchsentbeforethefailure.&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;(AC-3)&lt;/em&gt; &lt;tt&gt;RequestSentTimeStamp&lt;/tt&gt; stays NULL for the failed + stranded rows; set for any batch sent before the failure.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;%28AC3%29Servicehealthyafterwards%E2%80%94endpointstillreturns%7B%7B202%7D%7D%2Cnohostloopdeath.&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;(AC-3)&lt;/em&gt; Service healthy afterwards &#8212; endpoint still returns &lt;tt&gt;202&lt;/tt&gt;, no host-loop death.&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;%28AC5%29Afterrestoringconfigandretriggering%2Cbatchessendandstampnormally%28idempotentretryintact%29.&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;(AC-5)&lt;/em&gt; After restoring config and re-triggering, batches send and stamp normally (idempotent retry intact).&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&#9888;&#65039; Email-delivery caveat (do not skip):&lt;/em&gt; &quot;an alert email was sent&quot; must be verified by ACTUAL DELIVERY, not by the service logging a send. The SendGrid wrapper&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;Send&lt;/tt&gt; is fire-and-forget &lt;tt&gt;void&lt;/tt&gt; &#8212; success only means SendGrid &lt;em&gt;accepted&lt;/em&gt; the request (HTTP 202), NOT that it was delivered. Confirm via &lt;em&gt;SendGrid Activity&lt;/em&gt; AND the &lt;em&gt;recipient inbox / M365 quarantine&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Full canonical doc: &lt;tt&gt;_bmad-output/products/payments/04_ExpresseLane/enhancement/treasury-funding-send-error-handling/qa-verification.md&lt;/tt&gt; (also see &lt;tt&gt;solution.md&lt;/tt&gt; &#8594; &quot;QA verification&quot;). Coordinate with 
